# Craftflow Senior Architect & Full-stack Developer Instructions

## 1. Project Context
- **Name:** Craftflow — private creative assistant for writers and artists (novel writing + AI illustration).
- **Core Philosophy:** Human-in-the-loop (AI suggests, never overwrites), Local-first (Ollama/ComfyUI on local machine), Content Integrity (original drafts untouched).

## 2. Tech Stack
- **Backend:** Python 3.11, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy 2.0 (SQLite), Pydantic v2.
- **Frontend:** React 18 (Vite 5), JavaScript, Vanilla CSS-in-JS, dual-theme tokens in index.css.
- **AI:** Ollama `http://host.docker.internal:11434` (`dolphin-llama3` text, `qwen2.5vl:7b` vision) · ComfyUI `http://host.docker.internal:8188` (SDXL, ControlNet Union ProMax, IP-Adapter) · kohya_ss for LoRA training.
- Use `host.docker.internal` from containers, `localhost` when running directly.

## 3. Directory Structure
- `backend/main.py`: 16 routers, prefix `/api/v1`.
- `backend/app/api/`: routes only (art_generate.py is 3,075 lines — split plan: doc/2026-06-12_A1拆解規劃.md).
- `backend/app/services/` (+`ai/`): business logic — art/character/consistency/image_edit services, generation_jobs (async), generation_recorder, vram_manager, prompt_engine, lora_trainer, export_service.
- `backend/app/models|schemas/`: ORM + Pydantic (chapter_revision = snapshots, generation_history = reproducibility).
- `backend/app/core/`: config (.env, PERSONAL_STYLE_*), database, backup (periodic VACUUM INTO), state (runtime globals, reset on restart).
- `frontend/src/`: App.jsx (sidebar shell, bottom history), components/*Tab.jsx (CharacterTab 2,431 lines — split planned A2).
- `data/custom_workflows/`: ComfyUI workflows, API format required (Standard_V35 / _EyeFix A/B).
- `tools/Craftflow/`: legacy CLI, migrating into services/ai/.
- `doc/`: daily dev logs (`YYYY-MM-DD_開發記錄.md`, never edit old days) + planning docs (checkbox updates only).

## 4. Coding Standards & Rules
- Surgical updates only — no unrelated refactors.
- FastAPI router patterns; business logic in services/, models in models/, schemas in schemas/.
- Always handle Ollama/ComfyUI timeouts/errors — the app must not crash; long tasks need backend status + frontend progress.
- Non-destructive: analysis/rewrite results go to separate files/fields; NEVER overwrite user originals.
- Read before editing; propose and explain risk before applying.

## 5. Environment Pitfalls
- repo=LF, Windows tree=CRLF → sandbox git shows all files modified (false); normalize before staging.
- File-tool writes to mounted folders may truncate tails → write via shell, verify tail.
- Never commit `vite.config.js.timestamp-*.mjs`; SQLite must not be written from sandbox.
